#### Mobile apps

1. Can be developed as a web application or rich client application
2. Can support occasionally connected scenarios
3. Run on devices with limited hardware resources

#### Rich client apps

1. Usually developed as a stand-alone application
2. Can support disconnected or occasionally connected scenarios
3. Use the processing and storage resources of the local machine

#### Rich Internet Apps

1. Can support multiple platforms and browsers
2. Can be deployed over the internet
3. Are designed for rich media and graphical content
4. Run in the browser for maximum security
5. Can use the processing and storage resources of the local machine

#### Service apps

1. Can support multiple platforms and browsers
2. Support only connected scenarios
3. Use the processing and storage resources of the server

#### Web apps

1. Can support multiple platforms and browsers
2. Support only connected scenarios
3. Use the processing and storage resources of the server